# 9. 感謝の言葉

Akito: Huff... Huff...
Akito: Oh, Kamishiro...
Rui: Well done. Your performance was certainly what you'd expect from the headliners.
Akito: Thank you.
Akito: And you're up next.
Rui: Yes. I hope you enjoy the show.
Staff: Everyone, please get ready!
Tsukasa: Alright, this is it! Here we go!
Nene, Emu & Rui: Yeah! Yes!
Saki: It's almost time for Tsukasa and his troupe to perform! I can't wait!
Audience: The people who do the night show at PXL are supposed to be next!
Audience: Oh, WXS? That's awesome! I didn't realize they'd be performing at Shibuya Festa!
Rui: (Hehe. The audience sounds very excited.)
Rui: (Plus...)
Emu: Oh, it's Asahina! She came to watch!
Rui: Yes, I see her. I'm glad she decided to come.
Rui: (I don't know how much of an impact our show is going to have on her...)
Rui: But let's make this show one to remember.
Nanamin: Next, we have Wonderlands×Showtime! Take it away!
Mizuki: What do you think their show's gonna be like? I can't wait to find out!
Mafuyu: ...
Narrator: “There once was a demon who lived all alone.”
Narrator: “And this demon had one job... To corrupt humanity.”
Narrator: “As such, this demon became responsible for the downfall of several humans. However...”
Demon: “Heh heh heh! Finally! I have reached my 1,000th victim!”
Demon: ”A feat unmatched by others! Not even those from the underworld! All shall cheer and hail my name!”
Demon: “Alas...”
Demon: “Things have been far too easy as of late... I've accomplished my goal of reaching 1,000 victims, but feel no sense of satisfaction.”
Demon: “Is there no better way to entertain myself...?”
Little Demon: “Festival, festival♪ A fun, fun festival♪”
Demon: “Hm? That demon over there looks awfully small and weak...”
Demon: “But it seems rather happy. You there!”
Little Demon: “Hm? Can I help you?”
Demon: “What are you doing? You seem far too happy for your own good...”
Little Demon: “Oh, I was just about to put a festival together!”
Demon: “A festival...? Yes, I see... One held in the name of demons, which serves to corrupt humanity!”
Little Demon: “What? No!”
Little Demon: “I just want to have a festival where everyone can have fun and be happy! I don't want corrupting humanity to have anything to do with it!”
Demon: “Huh?”
Demon: “What kind of festival put on by a demon doesn't revolve around corrupting humans?! You are supposed to have them engage in merrymaking and encourage them to become more hedonistic...”
Little Demon: “No, I'm bored of doing that. I don't like how they essentially become zombies in the end...”
Little Demon: “Which is why I think a fun and happy festival would be much better!”
Little Demon: “We can put one on together! A happy, demonic festival that everyone can enjoy! Let's go!”
Demon: “H-Hey, don't yank me!”
Saki: Hehe. It's like Tsukasa and Emu in real life!
Shiho: It's funny how they're just being themselves, even though they're supposed to be scary demons.
Little Demon: “I brought a new recruit! It should be a lot easier to put on our festival now!”
Older Demon: “Ah, so there are other strange folk like us still around. Who exactly did you...? Huh?”
Older Demon: “Wait, this is the biggest and baddest demon of them all! The one who corrupted 1,000 humans! What's he doing here...?!”
Demon: “I was brought here all of a sudden...”
Older Demon: “This is bad! If the more powerful demons find out about us putting on a happy festival that has nothing to do with corrupting humans, we're going to be in big trouble.”
Little Demon: “We are? But I thought it'd be fun if we brought him along since he seemed so bored.”
Older Demon: “Argh! That's not the point! If the others find out, they'll lock us up in the underworld and make it so we can't come back to the human world!”
Little Demon: “Really?”
Older Demon: “Yes, really! Get it through that thick skull of yours already!”
Demon: “What fools... However... Hmm...”
Demon: “Did you make these decorations and costumes for this festival of yours?”
Older Demon: “Y-Yes... The human I used to follow around was someone who made outfits for festivals...”
Older Demon: “I was going to corrupt them, but they died of an illness before I could... The costumes they left behind were very beautiful, so I decided to try making copies of them.”
Older Demon: “Before I knew it, I was having fun.”
Demon: “I see... Fine, I'll play along since I have nothing better to do at the moment.”
Older Demon: “Really?! You will?!”
Demon: “Yes! I shall aid thee! And if I become bored, I'll just report you to the bosses for a tidy reward.”
Minori: Th-That's awful...! This demon really is evil!
Shizuku: He looks like the Tsukasa I'm used to seeing, but he really is quite good at playing less-than-savory characters.
Demon: “Now, where do you need me to begin? I should have no issues accomplishing whatever it is that you need of me.”
Older Demon: “Then, can you come up with ideas for our festival?”
Demon: “Yes, no problem! I know! We can get these humans intoxicated and...”
Older Demon: “No using charm potions on the humans.”
Little Demon: “Oh, one of us still needs to make the device for shooting fireworks!”
Demon: “Ah, that sounds fun! With my magic, I should be able to...”
Little Demon: “But no using magic! It's too dangerous!”
Demon: “Grr... This is becoming very bothersome...!!”
Kohane: Hehe. I always love Tsukasa's performances where he goes along with Emu and the others' antics...! He's so good at interacting with them!
Akito: Yeah, he is. Hang on. Isn't he just being himself for those parts?
Mafuyu: ...
Mizuki: Interesting. He's supposed to be this all-powerful, evil demon, but he's beginning to see how fun it is to put on a festival as he interacts with these demons that see things differently to him.
Mizuki: Which means, pretty soon...
Mafuyu: (I-It's him...)
Smiling Demon: “Ah, I heard you're the one who corrupted 1,000 humans. Congratulations!”
Demon: “Th-Thank you... However, it was but a trifle to me.”
Smiling Demon: “Indeed. But I was wondering why I hadn't seen you in the human world lately. What have you been up to?”
Demon: “Oh, I've been on vacation... It seemed like I was in need of a break is all!”
Smiling Demon: “A vacation? I see.”
Mafuyu: ...
Mafuyu: (He's walking normally...)
Mafuyu: (I guess his foot's fine now...)
Demon: “Stop! Unhand me at once!”
Little Demon: “P-Please, let us out!”
Older Demon: “How did you find out about us putting on a festival?! We didn't tell anyone...”
Smiling Demon: “Ah, I had a feeling... Demons like you lot appear from time to time.”
Smiling Demon: “Honestly, demons trying to make humans happy. How foolish...”
Demon: “Urgh...”
Demon: “Then, let me ask you this... Is corrupting humans that much fun? Is that what you truly wish to do?”
Mafuyu: (What he truly wishes to do...)
Smiling Demon: “This is not a matter of fun. We have an important role to play in this world.”
Demon: “Why are you prioritizing that?! Our role in this world doesn't matter! I... I just want to...”
Smiling Demon: “Shout all you want... You will receive your punishment shortly.”
Demon: “Blast...! What are we to do...?”
Little Demon: “They brought all our things for the festival here too. Does that mean they're going to throw them all away...?”
Demon: “Our things for the festival...? That's it!”
Older Demon: “Huh? What are you doing?”
Demon: “Here we are! This is the device I made for launching fireworks...!”
Demon: “We'll escape to the human world using this!”
Little Demon & Older Demon: “What?!”
Older Demon: “That's impossible! I mean, yes, we're imprisoned at the bottom of the abyss with no roof or ceiling in sight...”
Little Demon: “But if we don't make it and fall... We're goners...!!”
Demon: “I don't care... This is what I want to do.”
Demon: “I want to put on that festival with you two!”
Demon: “I'll go first! If I manage to succeed, follow me up!”
Demon: “Here we go! One, two... Three!”
Honami: T-Tsukasa's flying...!!
Shizuku: He's going higher than the stage lights...!
Akito: You've gotta be kidding me...
Mafuyu: (He's flying...)
Mafuyu: Incredible...
Kanade: Huh?
Demon: “It worked! I'm back in the human world! Come on up, you two!”
Little Demon & Older Demon: “Okay!”
Smiling Demon: “Hm...? What the? The cell's empty! What happened...?!”
Demon: “Hey! We're up here!”
Smiling Demon: “Huh...?! How did you escape...?!”
Demon: “That's for you to find out! In any case, we're going to have ourselves a festival!”
Demon: “You're also welcome to join us! We'll give you as much time as you need!”
Little Demon: “We'll be waiting!!”
Smiling Demon: “...! To think that they'd use that contraption to escape...”
Smiling Demon: “Still...”
Smiling Demon: “What I truly wish to do...”
Smiling Demon: “It may be worth thinking about...”
Demon: “Anyway, we're back in the human world.”
Demon: “So, it's time for our festival to commence!!”
Narrator: “And so, the demons held their festival for three days and nights. As a result, they were able to bring smiles to the faces of many humans. The end.”
Ichika: Their show was so good!
Toya: And the perfect performance for leading off the shows for Shibuya Festa's corporate sponsors.
Airi: Their costumes were really nice too! They had such a great trickster feel to them. I'd love to try something like that on if given the chance.
Mafuyu: ...
Kanade: That was really good. I'm glad we got to see it together, Mafuyu.
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu: Yes, me too...
Mizuki: Yeah! Rui's troupe put on such a good show! Li'l Bro and his team did an awesome performance too! Oh...
Rui: Good evening. Did you enjoy our show?
Mizuki: Yeah, it was amazing! I was so moved by the scene where Tsukasa flew! I still can't believe you made that device, Rui!
Ena: What?! You made that?!
Nene: Yes, he did... He has a bit of a talent for that.
Tsukasa: That's because our director here's a genius!
Nene: Says the person who was quivering before launch.
Tsukasa: Th-They don't need to know that!
Rui: Hehe. I hate to interrupt...
Rui: But I'd like to say how our show was only possible because of you, Asahina. Thank you very much for what you did.
Mafuyu: What...?
Rui: We were only able to do our show the way we did because you were kind enough to treat my injury.
Rui: Our shows mean quite a lot to me, so I can't even begin to express how grateful I am for your help.
Emu: Thank you so very much, Asahina!
Tsukasa: Yes, and we apologize for not thanking you sooner. We appreciate what you did and were able to put on a fantastic show as a result!
Nene: Thank you very much. If you like, please stop by the Wonder Stage for another show. We'd love to see you there.
Rui: From the bottom of my heart, thank you.
Mafuyu: Oh...
Mafuyu: Um, it was nothing... I'm just glad that I could help. Still...
Mafuyu: I enjoyed your show.
Mizuki: Hm? They seem like friends all of a sudden.
Kanade: Yes, they do...
Ena: Oh, since the show's over, wanna check out the stalls and exhibit? You don't have much time left, right, Mafuyu?
Mafuyu: Oh, right...
Mizuki: Alright, let's go!
